16/12/2003
BERN, Switzerland -- President Pascal Couchepin and his Romanian counterpart Ion Iliescu signed an agreement Monday (15 December) lifting visa requirements for Romanian visitors. 
The new travel regime would take effect 30 days after ratification by the respective parliaments. 
Monday's meeting was the first between presidents in 92 years of diplomatic relations. 
They discussed economic co-operation, border security, and measures against illegal trafficking. 
Couchepin praised Romania for its progress with EU accession reforms. 
(Rompres, Mediafax - 16/12/03)
